zoot suit a play by luis valdez events at stanford zoot suit a play by luis valdez facebook twitter email print add to calendar the 25th anniversary production of zoot suit casa zapata stanford university thursday saturday feb 23 25 2012 8 00pm this year marks the 25th year of the production of zoot suit which has been the centerpiece of casa zapata's residential programming since 1987 zoot suit is a compelling portrayal of the historic sleepy lagoon murder trial the story takes place in 1940's los angeles where the zoot suit riots war time hysteria and violent racism against mexican americans were at its highest peak the play will have three showings during parent's weekend on february 23rd 24th and 25th all of the performances are free and open to the public and feature live music dance numbers and a full ensemble led by director wilma bonet when ongoing every day from february 23 2012 through february 25 2012 8 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where casa zapata dining hall map audience general public faculty staff students tags arts performance drama sponsor sponsored by casa zapata and the residential arts program in residential education mecha de stanford and the charles f riddell fund contact 650 724 3657 nbonilla stanford edu admission reservations recommended for opening feb 23rd reserve tickets at http tinyurl com zootsuit2012 permalink http events stanford edu events 308 30833 last modified february 2 2012
